The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Advani starts title defence in style
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Advani starts title defence in style
                      
	Bangalore: Defending champion Pankaj Advani on Saturday started his journey in style defeating compatriot Prem Prakash in the World Billiards Championships time format. Advani, who annexed the point format of the Championship on Friday, outperformed Prakash 1735-703 in the league opener.         
	Veteran Geet Sethi, who lost to Advani in the points format, proved too good for his Irish opponent Aidan Murray winning 1939-167.         
	The other Indians, who won their opening league matches include Arvind Savur, Devendra Joshi and Sourav Kothari.         
	Other results: Larry Drennan (Ireland) bt Md Aslam (Sri Lanka) 781-485; Peter Gilchrist (Singapore) bt Raghoo Sinha (India) 1834-368; Shyam Jagtiani (India) bt Md Asim (India) 765-624; B Bhaskar (India) bt Brijesh Damani (India) 867-697; Praprut Chaithanasakun (Thailand) bt Gary Oliver (NZ) 1151-444; Rupesh Shah (India) bt Suriya Suwannasingh (Thai) 1299-462; Teik Chong Alan Puan (Sing) bt Gary Norman (EBOS) 957-301.           (PTI)                                                                                                                      
